    <h3 class="uw-accordion-header">
      I just declared a new major. Do I need to let ISS know?     </h3>

    <div class="uw-accordion-panel -uw-accordion-is-hidden">
      <div class="uw-accordion-panel-inner uw-clearfix">
        <p>Yes, you will need to submit the <a href="https://terradotta.wisc.edu/index.cfm?FuseAction=Abroad.ViewLink&amp;Parent_ID=61ADF84B-F9FD-D592-C1E9278EE7213EA1&amp;Link_ID=62C95064-F12A-D9DE-D2931D4006A97438">Addition/Change of Major</a> form on Terra Dotta if you have added a new major or changed majors.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  
    <h3 class="uw-accordion-header">
      How many credits do I need to enroll in?     </h3>

    <div class="uw-accordion-panel -uw-accordion-is-hidden">
      <div class="uw-accordion-panel-inner uw-clearfix">
        <p>According to I<a href="https://iss.wisc.edu/students/current-students/f1-information/full-time-enrollment/">SS enrollment policy</a>, to maintain your visa status, undergraduates must enroll in a minimum of 12 credits each fall and spring semester.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  
    <h3 class="uw-accordion-header">
      Can I take less than 12 credits in my last semester?     </h3>

    <div class="uw-accordion-panel -uw-accordion-is-hidden">
      <div class="uw-accordion-panel-inner uw-clearfix">
        <p>According to <a href="https://iss.wisc.edu/students/current-students/reduced-course-load/">ISS RCL policy</a>, students are eligible to take less than 12 credits if you need less than a full-time course load to complete your program of study in your final major.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  
    <h3 class="uw-accordion-header">
      How do I apply for RCL?    </h3>

    <div class="uw-accordion-panel -uw-accordion-is-hidden">
      <div class="uw-accordion-panel-inner uw-clearfix">
        <div>Students seeking a reduced course load (RCL) verification from a Data Science or Statistics major advisor must provide the information requested on the <a href="https://uwmadison.co1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_9L8LzAPRD4lOCG2">Stats/DS RCL Qualtrics form</a>.</div>
<div></div>
<div>Once your information has been reviewed you will be contacted by your advisor and may need to schedule an appointment, provide more information, or be asked to submit your Terra Dotta form.</div>
<div></div>
<div>You may need to review the <a href="https://iss.wisc.edu/students/current-students/reduced-course-load/">ISS website on RCL</a> to answer some questions on the form.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

  
    <h3 class="uw-accordion-header">
      Is my major STEM-designated for CPT and OPT?    </h3>

    <div class="uw-accordion-panel -uw-accordion-is-hidden">
      <div class="uw-accordion-panel-inner uw-clearfix">
        <p>Both the Statistics and Data Science majors are STEM-designated degree programs by the U.S. Department of Homeland Security (DHS). You can view a list of all <a href="https://studyinthestates.dhs.gov/stem-opt-hub/additional-resources/eligible-cip-codes-for-the-stem-opt-extension">STEM-OPT eligible programs</a>.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

  
    <h3 class="uw-accordion-header">
      Am I eligible to study abroad?    </h3>

    <div class="uw-accordion-panel -uw-accordion-is-hidden">
      <div class="uw-accordion-panel-inner uw-clearfix">
        <p>Some International students (holding an F-1 or J-1 visa) do choose to study abroad. Students considering this option should review the <a href="https://studyabroad.wisc.edu/student-identity/international-students-f1-and-j1-visa-holders/">Study Abroad</a> website with info specific to International students.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

